The popular adrenaline rousing Swannies Racing Series will host a 200 km endurance race on Ysterberg just outside Polokwane on 3 August.
Quad bike and two wheeler enthusiasts are invited to join the event as it promises to be an unforgettable event which will test bikers’ skills and most important their endurance during the race.
Trophies are up for grabs to all podium winners in various categories of quad and two wheel bikes.
Registration fees are R450 per bike and visitors will have to pay R20 per vehicle to be part of the challenging event. Registration can be done on the race day prior to the start which is scheduled for 10:00.
Participants can travel on the R101 until they find the Geyser turn-off and follow the signs to the venue. Alternatively make use of the GPS location 24°02’07.6″S 29°14’06.9″E
Food and drinks will be on sale.
For more information contact Peet or Swannie Swanepoel on 083 469 0138 or 071 859 6924 respectively.
